{{Use Indian English|date=September 2017}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}} {{Infobox person | name = Varsha Usgaonkar | image = Varsha-Usgaonkar-Crop.jpg | image_size = | caption = Varsha Usgaonkar in March 2015 | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1968|2|28}} | years_active= 1987–present | birth_place = [[Goa]], [[India]] | occupation = Actress, model | spouse = Ajay Sharma | children = | parents = | relatives = | other_names = }}
'''Varsha Usgaonkar''' (born 28 February 1968) is an [[India]]n film actress from [[Goa]], who has worked in various [[Bollywood]] and [[Marathi cinema|Marathi]] movies as the leading lady. During the 1990s, she was the most popular actress in [[Marathi cinema]].<ref name="mouthshut">{{cite web|url=http://m.mouthshut.com/review/Varsha-Usgaonkar-review-mqtqumnonn|title=VARSHA USGAONKAR - Review, Wallpapers, Movies, VARSHA USGAONKARmovie List, Videos, Songs, Varsha Usgaonkar - mouthshut.com|publisher=m.mouthshut.com|accessdate=3 January 2015}}</ref>
==Career== Varsha Usgaonkar first shot to fame in 1982 as the lead heroine in the super-hit [[Marathi language|Marathi]] stage play ''Brahmachari''. Subsequently, she quickly rose to one of the top heroines in the [[Marathi language|Marathi]] film industry with super-hits such as ''Gammat Jammat'', ''Hamal De Dhamal'', ''Saglikade Bombabomb'', ''[[Sawat Majhi Ladki]]'', ''Shejari Shejari'', ''[[Ek Hota Vidushak]]'', ''[[Lapandaav]]'', ''[[Aflatoon (1991 film)|Aflatoon]]'' and others. She has also starred as the lead actress in the [[Bollywood]] films ''[[Ghar Aaya Mera Pardesi]]'' and ''[[Pathreela Raasta]]''. In 2005, she appeared in the [[Bollywood]] films ''[[Mangal Pandey: The Rising]]'' and ''[[Mr Ya Miss]]'' as a supporting actress. In the [[Faisal Saif]]-directed controversial Hindi feature film, ''[[Jigyaasa]]'', she played mother to [[Hrishitaa Bhatt]]. Usgaonkar started her television career in the 1988 playing role of [[Uttarā (Mahabharata)|Uttara]], wife of [[Abhimanyu]] and mother of [[Parikshit]], (the future of the Bharat Dynasty TV serial ''[[Mahabharat (1988 TV series)|Mahabharata]]'').The role lead her to many Hindi movies offers and most of them failed to create a box office success. She also played role of Roopmati (Snake Queen) in 1994 TV serial ''[[Chandrakanta (TV series)|Chandrakanta]]''. She has appeared in the Marathi shows ''[[Aakash Zep]]'' and ''[[Eka Mekansathi]]'', and she has also acted in the [[Hindi]] television serials ''[[Alvida Darling]]'',<ref>{{cite news |title=I feel sad and deprived, I do miss Chamatkar|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/Storyold/84269/|accessdate=3 January 2015|newspaper=Indian Express|publisher=indianexpress.com}}</ref> ''[[Tanha (TV series)|Tanha]]'' and ''[[Anhonee (TV series)|Anhonee]]''.
One of her most prominent performance is from the TV Serial ''[[Jhansi Ki Rani]]'' in the 1990s on [[Doordarshan]], where she played the lead character of [[Rani Lakshmibai]].
Usgaonkar has also sung in a [[Konkani]] music album ''Roop Tujem Laita Pixem'', with Ulhas Buyao.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rockandraaga.in/node/103|title=Rock and Raaga|year=2010|accessdate=3 January 2015|publisher=rockandraaga.in}}</ref>
==Personal life== [[File:Varsha-Ajay.jpg|thumb|right|Usgaonkar with husband Ajay Shankar in 2014]] Varsha is a [[Konkani people|Konkani]].<ref name="thehindu">{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-karnataka/konkani-parishads-silver-jubilee-session-in-february/article3241133.ece|title=Konkani Parishad's silver jubilee session in February - The Hindu|publisher=thehindu.com|accessdate=3 January 2015}}</ref><ref name="google">{{cite book|title=Konkani People: Guru Dutt, Girish Karnad, Shyam Benegal, Ravindra Kelekar, Eesha Koppikhar, Basti Vaman Shenoy, Shankar Nag, Deepika Padukone|author=Wikipedia, S.|date=2011|publisher=General Books|isbn=9781233060511|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sxQdygAACAAJ|accessdate=3 January 2015}}</ref> She is the daughter of Goa's former [[Goa Legislative Assembly|Deputy Speaker]] [[A. K. S. Usgaonkar]]. She has two sisters, Dr. Mrs. Tosha Kurade and Mrs. Manisha Tarcar.<ref name="navhindtimes">{{cite web|url=http://www.navhindtimes.in/iexplore/goa-s-emerald-eyed-sridevi|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140102211943/http://www.navhindtimes.in/iexplore/goa-s-emerald-eyed-sridevi |archive-date=2014-01-02 |dead-url=yes|title=Goa’s emerald eyed ‘Sridevi’ &#124; iGoa|accessdate=3 January 2015}}</ref> Usgaonkar married in March 2000 to Ajay Sharma, son of Indian film music director Ravishankar Sharma or [[Ravi (music director)|Bombay Ravi]].<!-- broken<ref>{{cite news|last=Bhagat|first=Shama|title=‘My son and his wife want to throw me out’|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/tabloid/sunday-chronicle/heartitude/%E2%80%98my-son-and-his-wife-want-throw-me-out%E2%80%99-709|accessdate=28 December 2011|newspaper=Deccan Chronicle|date=17 April 2011|author2=Ravi Shankar Sharma}}</ref>--><ref name="outlookindia">{{cite web|url=http://m.outlookindia.com/story.aspx?sid=1&aid=672734|title=Redirection From Mobile URL|publisher=m.outlookindia.com|accessdate=3 January 2015}}</ref>
