'''William S. Yellow Robe Jr.''' (born February 4, 1960{{citation needed|date=September 2016}}) is an [[Assiniboine people|Assiniboine]] actor, author, director, educator, playwright, and poet.<ref name=amerinda/>

==Life and career==
A member of the [[Assiniboine and Sioux Tribes of the Fort Peck Indian Reservation]], Yellow Robe was raised by his mother on the Fort Peck Indian Reservation in [[Montana]].<ref>{{cite journal |last=Uno |first=Roberta |title=Interview: William Yellow Robe |journal=MELUS |date=Fall 1989 |volume=16 |issue=3 |page=83 |doi=10.2307/467568 |last2=Robe |first2=William Yellow}}</ref> He studied writing and performing arts at the [[University of Montana]].<ref>{{cite journal |last=Pulitano |first=Elvira |title=Telling Stories through the Stage: A Conversation with William Yellow Robe |journal=[[Studies in American Indian Literatures]] |date=Spring 1998 |volume=10 |issue=1 |page=19}}</ref>

Yellow Robe's works have been performed in venues across the United States, including the [[Penumbra Theatre Company]] in St. Paul;<ref>{{cite web |title=Grandchildren of the Buffalo Soldiers |url=http://penumbratheatre.org/component/option,com_penumbra/task,viewpage/Itemid,54/showid,240/id,188/sid,/ |work=Penumbra |publisher=Penumbra Theatre |accessdate=2015-03-24}}</ref> the [[Public Theater]] in New York;<ref>{{cite web |first=Adam |last=Hetrick |title=William S. YellowRobe Jr.'s ''Thieves'' Arrives at the Public |url=http://www.playbill.com/news/article/153306-William-S-YellowRobe-Jrs-Thieves-Arrives-at-the-Public-Aug-3 |work=Playbill |publisher=Playbill |date=August 3, 2011 |accessdate=2015-03-24}}</ref>  the [[Trinity Repertory Company]] in Providence, RI;<ref>{{cite web |title=Past Seasons |url=http://www.trinityrep.com/about_us/history/past_seasons.php |work=Trinity Repertory Company |publisher=Trinity Repertory Company |accessdate=2013-03-19 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120228231233/http://www.trinityrep.com/about_us/history/past_seasons.php |archivedate=2012-02-28}}</ref> and the Smithsonian's [[National Museum of the American Indian]] in Washington, D.C.<ref>{{cite web |title=National Museum of the American Indian Presents Production of Grandchildren of the Buffalo Soldiers |url=http://newsdesk.si.edu/releases/national-museum-american-indian-presents-production-grandchildren-buffalo-soldiers |work=Newsdesk |publisher=Smithsonian |accessdate=2015-03-24}}</ref> He is a member of Penumbra, as well as the Ensemble Studio Theater,<ref>{{cite web |first=Hanay |last=Geiogamah |title=Interview with William S. Yellow Robe Jr. (2007) |url=http://hemisphericinstitute.org/hemi/en/hidvl/hidvl-int-native-theater/item/1354-ntfest-wsyellowrobe |work=Hemispheric Institute Digital Video Library |publisher=Hemispheric Institute of Performance and Politics |accessdate=2015-03-24}}</ref> Amerinda, Inc.,<ref name=amerinda>{{cite web |title=William S. Yellow Robe Jr. |url=http://www.amerinda.org/naar/yellowrobe/playwright/playwright.htm |work=Amerinda.org |publisher=Amerinda |accessdate=2015-03-24}}</ref> and the advisory board for Red Eagle Soaring Theater Company for Native youth.<ref>{{cite news |title=Acclaimed playwright William S. Yellow Robe Jr. to read works at Hangin' Art Gallery |url=http://www.charkoosta.com/2012/2012_11_08/Playwright_Yellowrobe_at_Hangin_Art_Gallery-110812.html |accessdate=2015-03-24 |work=Char-Koosta News |date=November 8, 2012}}</ref>

Yellow Robe has also taught at the [[Institute of American Indian Arts]], [[Brown University]],<ref>{{cite news |last=McElwain |first=Diana |title=William Yellow Robe: No One's Stray Dog |url=http://mainecampus.com/2003/04/21/william-yellow-robe-no-ones-stray-dog/ |accessdate=2015-03-24 |work=Bangor Daily News |date=April 21, 2003}}</ref>  and the [[University of Maine]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Faculty — William Yellow Robe |url=https://english.umaine.edu/faculty/william-yellow-robe/ |work=Department of English |publisher=University of Maine |accessdate=2015-03-24}}</ref>

